  "doc_id": "16195",
  "text": "Social avoidance is a well-characterized outcome of RSD [CITATION_1] . We observed that both WT and ZnT3 KO mice became avoidant of an aggressive CD-1 mouse following RSD. Only WT mice avoided a novel conspecific, however; stressed ZnT3 KO mice did not. Given previous reports that male ZnT3 KO mice show increased [CITATION_2] and decreased (Yoo et al., 2016) social interaction with a novel mouse, it is worth highlighting that we found no baseline differences in sociability; interaction time with either a conspecific or a CD-1 mouse did not differ between genotypes in non-stressed controls.",
